SIMPLE: shug
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shug
<hw>Shug</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Shrug</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To writhe the body so as to
produce friction against one's clothes, as do those who have the
itch.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to crawl; to sneak.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There I 'll <qex>shug</qex> in and get a noble countenance.</q>
<rj><qau>Ford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shumac</ent>⟦br⟧
